WorkItem.Description:
As soon as your source file contains an accent, the compiler throws an error :
```
/*

Compile Error. 
See error list for details
 error TS5004: Could not find file: '<path>\file1.ts'.


*/
```

This code compiles :
```
var chaine : string = "":
chaine = "hehe";
```

This one doesn't :
```
var chaine : string = "":
chaine = "héhé";
```

Neither does this one (string in comment) :
```
var chaine : string = "":
//chaine = "hô";
```
